ze=1> The following bi-laws have been approved by majority vote of the High Council:<br>
<br>
-No charging other Guild members for your trade skill services beyond the cost of materials. <br>
<br>
-Contribute to website content with screenshots, stories, etc. Encourage new members to visit the site and fill out the Guild Application. <br>
<br>
-Do not associate with known enemies, especially those of enemy guilds. <br>
<br>
-If you are grouped and your group runs into trouble, do not leave someone to return alone for their corpse. <br>
<br>
-Do not divulge information about guild activities to non-members. <br>
<br>
-Take up all grievances with other members with an Officer privately before taking any action. <br>
<br>
-Must be active, play at least once a week. <br>
<br>
-All members of the guild to be treated as individuals and equally. <br>
<br>
-The Guild does not officially sponsor a members' trade profession. However, should a guild member wish to help out a member's trade, it is done solely on a voluntary basis and all arrangements are made between the 2 members. <br>
<br>
-All members must have their guild tags showing at all times; role-play is allowed, anonymous is not allowed. The only exception to this is when a Full-member wants to start a new character. While the character is under level 12 the character MUST be anon.<br>
<br>
-No defaming or slandering the Guild name. <br>
<br>
-Members must make every reasonable effort to attend Guild Events and Festivals. <br>
<br>
-Any member that leaves the guild cannot rejoin in the future. All cases of a character wishing to return will be reveiwed by the High Council and House of Lords.<br>
<br>
-Items that are handed to guild members from other guild members as &quot;gifts&quot; are considered guild property and cannot be sold. The item when not used any longer is to be handed down to another member in the guild. That member must also hand the item down. When an item cannot be handed down any further, it is given to the treasurer character for storage in the bank until such time a new member may need it, or it will be sold and all monies from the item will be returned to the guild fund. <br>
<br>
The following was discussed and approved in separate motions individually:<br>
<br>
-Players can have no characters on the Quellious server in any guild other than Asylum's Gate<br>
